column3:
Cases are under heading "Cases identified in North Carolina among unvaccinated and vaccinated people during January 1, 2021 — [date]", likely towards the end of the PDF. Deaths are under the heading "What is the risk of dying of COVID-19 for people who are vaccinated versus unvaccinated?"

For BI hospitalization data, "Patients are counted as vaccinated if they provide proof of vaccination or if their vaccination status can be verified through North Carolina’s Covid-19 Vaccination 
Management System (CVMS). Patients who are not vaccinated, partially vaccinated, cannot provide proof of vaccine or whose vaccination status cannot be confirmed in CVMS are categorized as unvaccinated. "

Click on Breakthrough. Number, percent and number per 100,000

-can download daily case by vax rate per 100k

The breakthrough numbers only represent a subset of all COVID-19 hospitalizations in Nebraska. The DHHS does not have access to individual patient identifiers for all COVID-19 hospitalizations. Additionally, DHHS does not have all vaccination data due to missing data from some federal entities that do not report to the state, including through federal entities, such as the Indian Health Service, the Department of Veterans Affairs, the Department of Defense, and the Federal Retail Pharmacy Program
